description:
Great as a snack or party/picnic food: VEGAN TUNA SALAD SANDWICH. Its so simple to make mix everything in a bowl then adjust seasoning to your liking! Its versatile so feel free to add your twist. Kain na, lets eat!

Ingredients:
2 cups canned chickpeas/garbanzo beans 
1 small red onions, minced
1 celery stick, thinly sliced 
4 pieces nori seaweed, cut to small strips 
3 pieces green onions, sliced
1 cup vegan mayo, or more to taste (you can use store bought or make your own mayo using the recipe from Filipino Vegan
3-4 tablespoons apple cider vinegar (or regular vinegar if thats all you have)
3 tablespoons sugar, or more to taste 
3 teaspoons Dijon mustard/regular mustard, or more to taste 
Lemon juice from 1/2 medium lemon
Few pinches salt and pepper 
2 teaspoons sweet pickle relish, or more to taste 
1/4-1/2 cup vegan tuna (optional) 
Vegan sliced bread upon serving 
Lettuce and tomatoes upon serving 

Directions:
In a bowl, mash the chickpeas. You can use a potato masher, or back of a ladle, or a fork, or a food processor. Mash until you have chunky bits.

Add the rest of the ingredients and adjust seasoning to taste.

Assemble with bread, lettuce, and tomatoes. Or you can refrigerate up to 3-5 days.
